nodes.bodyText:
Is that extra LOOK_AHEAD trie worth it? Since it is just a copy of the CACHE one with the extra whitespace, wouldn't something like the following be as fast and avoid duplication?
HttpMethod method = CACHE.getBest(buffer, 0, buffer.remaining());
if (method == null)
    return null;

int whitespaceIndex = method.name().length();
if (buffer.remaining() == whitespaceIndex)
    return null;

byte b = buffer.get(whitespaceIndex);
return b == ' ' ? method : null;

